wikipedia_page.main: George William Hamstead (born 24 January 1946) is an English former professional footballer who played as a winger in the Football League for York City, Barnsley, Bury and Rochdale and was on the books of Rotherham United without making a league appearance. He served as reserve team coach at Bury after retiring from playing.
